@startuml vinijmoura_Azure-DevOps

!define RECTANGLE class

RECTANGLE "Azure DevOps" as AzureDevOps
RECTANGLE "PowerShell Scripts" as PowerShell
RECTANGLE "Azure SQL Database" as SQLDatabase
RECTANGLE "Power BI" as PowerBI

RECTANGLE "Custom Visuals" as CustomVisuals
RECTANGLE "Static Resources" as StaticResources

AzureDevOps -right-> PowerShell : Extract data
PowerShell -right-> SQLDatabase : Transform & Load
SQLDatabase -right-> PowerBI : Query data
CustomVisuals -up-> PowerBI : Enhance
StaticResources -up-> PowerBI : Theme

note bottom of PowerShell
  Extracts data from:
  - Users & Access
  - Projects & Processes
  - Repositories
  - Pipelines
  - Teams
  - Artifacts
  - Environments
  - Task Groups
  - Service Hooks
  - Extensions
end note

note bottom of SQLDatabase
  Stores data in tables:
  - AreaPermissions
  - VariableGroups
  - FeedPackageVersions
  - EnvironmentsDeploys
  - ProcessesWorkItemsFields
  - TeamSettingsBoards
  - PersonalAccessTokens
  - ReleaseDefinitionsClassic
  etc.
end note

note bottom of PowerBI
  Visualizes data with:
  - Custom visuals
  - Themed reports
  - Interactive dashboards
end note

@enduml